        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to provide support, rehabilitation, and empowerment to persons with disabilities through financial assistance for healthcare, education, vocational training, and assistive devices.",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The &amp;quot;Welfare Services for Disabled Persons&amp;quot; under the Mizoram Grant-in-Aid framework focuses on improving the quality of life of persons with disabilities by supporting voluntary organizations in delivering specialized services. Beneficiaries include persons with locomotor, visual, hearing, and mental disabilities, and multiple disabilities such as cerebral palsy and autism.\nThe scheme supports activities like vocational training, early detection, medical treatment, rehabilitation, and the provision of assistive devices. It also promotes awareness regarding the rights of disabled persons and supports the establishment of special schools and institutions.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "> **Rehabilitation &amp; Training:**\n\n\n- Vocational training for self-employment.\n- Early detection and intervention services.\n\n> **Medical Support:**\n\n\n- Treatment and rehabilitation services.\n- HIV/AIDS care for disabled persons.\n\n> **Assistive Devices:**\n\n\n- Prosthetics, mobility aids, hearing aids, Braille equipment.\n- Education Support.\n- Special schools and vocational centres.\n\n> **Awareness:**\n\n\n- Awareness programmes on disability rights.\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
